Node.Notes: Meaning of this word uncertain. Tree assumes: the Jews, namely the villagers, namely the ones who live in unwalled towns. See WBC commentary for alternative.
Interpretation of write here as a decree, bookended by v. 32, would resolve the objection that makes little sense to state that they are writing to confirm the letter that they are writing.
This letter of Purim the second one appears to refer forward to v. 30 and not back to the letter Mordecai wrote in v. 20, which is the first about Purim.
